<h2>3. FINT</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="529" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-1300x529.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9614" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-1300x529.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-400x163.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-768x313.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-1536x625.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-860x350.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-430x175.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-700x285.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria-150x61.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fint-Nigeria.png 1761w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>Fint is a peer to peer quick loan platform, it connects voluntary investors with prospective borrowers. This organisation offers products such as Asset-Backed Loans, Agriculture loans, Power, Insurance, and Real Estate loans.&nbsp;</p>



<p><a href="https://fint.ng/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fint</a>&nbsp;“seeks to connect borrowers looking for affordable loans with lender looking for attractive deals. Consequently, on this platform, you can either opt-in as a lender or a borrower, of which the lender/investor is promised up to 39% per annum on the invested sum. See below for requirements and loan range.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>You can apply for loans or invest from ₦20,000 to ₦1,200,000 payable within a period of 3 months to 12 months. You can easily calculate your loan and the interest payable with the Fint website calculator.</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>To use Fint’s services you have to sign up with your personal details, these include your full name, valid National ID card, address, and email. You will also be required to satisfy your loan capacity by providing your bank statement and a recent utility bill. Once your application is approved, you will be connected with the investor who will then fund your account.</p>



<h2>4. C24</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="645" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-1300x645.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9615" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-1300x645.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-400x198.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-768x381.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-1536x762.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-860x426.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-430x213.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-700x347.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria-150x74.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/c24-Nigeria.png 1803w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p><a href="https://c24ng.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">C24</a>&nbsp;is also a Nigerian online quick loan lender which promises to “help their clients reach their financial goals by offering great rates, unprecedented service, and fewer fees.” The company offers business loans, personal loans, and quick cash loans.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>C24 allows you to apply for up to ₦5,000,000 depending on whether you are applying for a business, person or quick cash loan. Note that the rate payable also depends on the nature of the loan.</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>To use C24 services you have to complete a 4-step online application form, the content includes:</p>



<ul><li>Check your eligibility for a loan and sign up with your personal details (note that you must be 22 years – 58 years old to possess the capacity to apply,</li><li>The second step is to provide valid means of identification and details of your next of kin.</li><li>Next step is to provide your employment info or details, take for example your contract of employment document.</li><li>The last step is to provide your current financial status by uploading your most recent bank statement.</li><li>Now you can input the amount of money you wish to borrow, and how long it will take you to pay back (which must fall within a period of 3 to 12 months</li><li>After your application is approved, you get credited within a matter of hours.</li></ul>



<h2>5. Fastcredit &#8211; Quick loan lender</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="523" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-1300x523.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9616" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-1300x523.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-400x161.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-768x309.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-1536x617.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-860x346.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-430x173.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-700x281.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria-150x60.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Fastcredit-Nigeria.png 1831w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>Fastcredit is one of the well-established quick loan lenders in Nigeria, it has up to six service outlets situated in Lagos, Abuja, Ondo, Ogun, Ibadan, and Victoria Island. It also has a detailed website where clients can peruse all that the platform has to offer.&nbsp;<a href="https://fastcredit-ng.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fastcredit</a>&nbsp;promises loans with attractive rates to fit the budget of their clients.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This Fintech company offers up to ₦3,000,000 loan depending on the category you opt for.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>Fastcredit offers SME Loans, Personal Loans, Corporate Partnership (group) loans, and Public Sector loans.</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>You do not need to have collateral or guarantor to apply for loans</p>



<ul><li>You are required to repay within 3 to 12 months.</li><li>Upload your bank statement of the recent 6 months.</li><li>Upload a copy of your Workplace ID card,</li><li>Input your personal details in the application form online.</li><li>Upload your national identity card and your current address.</li></ul>



<p>You will receive your funds the same day the loan is approved.</p>



<h2>6. GTB &#8211; Quick Credit</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="429" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-1300x429.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9617" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-1300x429.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-400x132.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-768x253.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-1536x507.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-860x284.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-430x142.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-700x231.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria-150x49.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/GTB-Quick-Credit-Nigeria.png 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>Guaranteed Trust Bank (GTB) is one of the most popular financial institutions in Nigeria, and in order to serve their customer better have created the Quick Credit platform. This subsidiary branch of GTB aims at giving affordable personal loans to Nigerians at a fixed price of 1.75% of the loan received.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.gtbank.com/personal-banking/loans/quick-credit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Quick Credit</a>&nbsp;is more of a personal loan plan available to both salary and non-salary earners. You can apply for a loan sum from ₦10,000 to ₦5,000,000 which you have to pay back within a period of 6 to 12 months. GTB promises that you will not be charged any extra charges or management fee.</p>



<p>To apply for Quick Credit you have to own a bank account with GTB. Upon registering with GTB, the platform is already integrated with your personal details, your home address, your bank statement, and your BVN. You can then proceed to apply for the loan.</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<ul><li>You must be 18 years and not older than 59 years.</li><li>You must have a GTB account.</li><li>You must have a minimum monthly deposit of ₦20,000 in your account or earn at least ₦10,000 net monthly salary.</li><li>You must have satisfactory credit reports.</li><li>You must not have pending debts.</li><li>Your account must not have a history of dud cheques.</li></ul>



<h2>7. Pettycash</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="484" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-1300x484.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9618" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-1300x484.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-400x149.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-768x286.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-1536x572.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-860x320.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-430x160.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-700x261.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria-150x56.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Pettycash-Nigeria.png 1887w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>From the name of the company, you already know that&nbsp;<a href="https://pettycash.com.ng/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pettycash</a>&nbsp;does not offer huge loans, and as a matter of fact, the highest you can apply for is ₦50,000 or 20% of your salary. Pettycash also has an investment option where willing lenders can invest their money for future interests. The platform also promises to require no collateral and to fund your account within a matter of 5 minutes.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<ul><li>Personal Loans where customers can apply for 20% of their monthly salary which must not fall below ₦30,000.</li><li>Federal Staff Loan where federal government workers can apply for funds ranging from ₦5,000 to ₦50,000.</li><li>Pettycash+ that offers salary earners an emergency loan of up to ₦5,000 within 5 minutes.</li><li>Pending loan types: Pettycash is also working on loan categories for NYSC (Corpers’ ₦1,000 to ₦5,000 loan) and selected market women.</li></ul>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>Note that the repayment rate depends on the type of loan you are applying for and the time of repayment, take, for example, a loan of ₦5,000 for 15 days only require you to pay back ₦5,625, whereas, you have to pay ₦6,250 if the loan repayment time is 30 days. You are also required to;</p>



<ul><li>Submit your bank account details</li><li>Input your email address and other personal details.</li></ul>



<h2>8. Social lenders</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="554" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-1300x554.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9619" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-1300x554.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-400x170.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-768x327.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-1536x655.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-860x367.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-430x183.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-700x298.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria-150x64.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Social-Lenders-Nigeria.png 1863w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>This is a unique online quick loan lender. They award loans to customers based on their social media reputation.&nbsp;<a href="https://www.sociallenderng.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Social Lender&nbsp;</a>simply requires you to sign up with either your LinkedIn, Facebook or Twitter and uses its proprietary social algorithm to calculate the client’s reputation score.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This score, in turn, determines the likelihood of your loan approval. Social Lender partners with Sterling Bank, TechStars, Bincom, and Barclays Accelerators to make the business go smoothly.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>Social Lender will give you a personal loan based on the strength of your social reputation. Know that you can only apply for a minimum of ₦1,000 up to a maximum of ₦100,000. New users can only get a maximum of ₦10,000 for their first few transactions.</p>



<p><strong>How to apply&nbsp;</strong></p>



<p>Connect with any of your social media platforms, and wait for your account to get approved. Once your account is approved, you can then apply via any of the following available methods;</p>



<ul><li>Web – Apply via the Social Lender website.</li><li>SMS – Apply for up to ₦10,000 by texting SOCIALLENDER + (Space) + AMOUNT to 30812 then wait for about 10 minutes to get the fund in your bank account.</li><li>USSD – Dial the code *348*3# to see your loan options. Note that as at 11/6/2019 the Social Lender USSD option is only available for 9mobile network users.</li><li>Mobile APP – Download the Social Lender App from Playstore or your preferred Appstore then explore to see your options, social score, and all it takes to apply for loans.</li></ul>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<ul><li>Have a reputable social media account (Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn)</li><li>Have a valid National ID card.</li><li>Input your bank details.</li><li>You are required to pay back within 1 month.</li><li>Your interest payment ranges from 5% to 20% depending on nature and risk attached to the loan requested.</li></ul>



