<p>LAPO (MFB)’s “SME Loan” focuses mainly on Small and Medium-scale Enterprises as the product was established to facilitate small and medium businesses in Nigeria.&nbsp;<a href="https://www.lapo-nigeria.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LAPO “SME” loan</a>&nbsp;requires no collateral, provides for professional financial advice in case needed, and promises a flexible repayment of loan structure.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>LAPO (MFB) SME loan is a business loan product from which you can apply for up to ₦5,000,000 for a promised flexible rate.</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<ul><li>Your National ID card or any other means of identification that states your age and current home address. (you can use your voter’s card; driver’s license or international passport).</li><li>A recent utility bill.</li><li>A loan application letter to show your interest in the loan.</li><li>Complete the application form you are given.</li><li>Two guarantors to stand for your credibility.</li><li>4 recent passport photographs.</li></ul>



<h2>10. Carbon (Formerly Paylater)</h2>



