<p>AELLA Fintech platform offers both individuals and corporate entities a chance to take loans or invest for future interests. The quick loan lenders allow customers to satisfy their emergency situations with a payback interest that is determined by the length of time it took you to pay back.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p><a href="https://aellaapp.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AELLA credit</a>&nbsp;offers personal and business loans which range from ₦1,500 to ₦90,000 payable within a period of 30 to 60 days, and with a monthly interest rate of 4% to 29%. Also, note that you get to borrow even more loans at much cheaper rates if you pay back on time and borrow more frequently.</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>You do not need collateral or guarantor to use AELLA’s services. All you need to do is:</p>



<ul><li>Download the AELLA app on your mobile device.</li><li>Register with your personal detail which includes your full name and current address.</li><li>Fill the application form,&nbsp;</li><li>Wait for the approval of your loan request,</li><li>Then receive your cash within a few minutes if approved.</li></ul>



<h2>12. Migo (9mobile)</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="560" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-1300x560.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9623" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-1300x560.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-400x172.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-768x331.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-1536x661.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-860x370.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-430x185.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-700x301.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria-150x65.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Migo-Nigeria.png 1858w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p><a href="https://www.migo.ng/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Migo is a Nigerian quick loan platform</a>&nbsp;powered by 9mobile with a major priority in the swiftness of the loan services, this is why they do not require you to upload any document, just a few clicks and you are good to go.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>Migo offers both capital loan for businesses and quick personal loans. However, they calculate your creditworthiness by checking your bank records via your BVN, in other words, you only get credited if the platform deems it fit that you have the ability to pay back. You can apply for up to ₦500,000, however, the earlier you pay back the lesser your payback rate which starts from 5% and grows over a period of 14 to 30 days.</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>Migo allows you to take your loan by completing the following process:</p>



<ul><li>Input your phone number.</li><li>Enter the One Time Password (OTP) that was sent to your phone number.</li><li>Pick the loan type that suits your budget.</li><li>Input your bank and credit card details.</li><li>Then wait a few minutes for the alert if your loan request gets approved.</li></ul>



<h2>13. Zedvance</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="509" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-1300x509.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9624" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-1300x509.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-400x157.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-768x301.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-1536x601.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-860x337.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-430x168.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-700x274.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria-150x59.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Zedvance-Nigeria.png 1842w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p><a href="https://zedvance.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Zedvance is a Nigerian Fintech company</a>&nbsp;that aims at “financially empowering Nigerians with plans to do more.” This platform offers up to ₦5,000,000 to be paid back within a period of 18 months. You can also enjoy up to ₦50,000 for free by referring your friends to also take loans on the platform.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<ul><li><strong>Zedvance Nano:</strong>&nbsp;Funds your loan instantly into your bank account without any stringent requirement.</li><li><strong>Zedvance Payroll:</strong>&nbsp;a product that allows salary earners to apply for up to ₦5,000,000 to be paid back within 18 months.</li><li><strong>Zedvance Business:</strong>&nbsp;this service at November 2019 is not available yet but it promises a huge financial push for businesses wishing to grow.</li></ul>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>To use Zedvance’s you have to:</p>



<ul><li>Create an account with the platform via the website or through MoneyPal app (powered by Zedvance) or by sending “Zee” a chat on Whatsapp @09060003933.</li><li>Proceed to the loan application form and select the loan category that suits your purpose.</li><li>Give answers to questions asked about your Identity and your current home address.</li><li>Receive your money within few minutes after your application is approved.&nbsp;</li></ul>



<h2>14. Rosabon Finance</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="595" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-1300x595.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9625" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-1300x595.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-400x183.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-768x351.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-1536x703.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-860x394.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-430x197.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-700x320.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria-150x69.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Rosabon-Finance-Nigeria.png 1838w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p><a href="https://www.rosabon-finance.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Rosabon Finance</a>&nbsp;company is also one of those quick loan lenders in Nigeria with high priority for fast transactions and ease in the application for quick cash online. In their words “Rosabon loan is an innovative lifestyle product that allows individuals who are in emergency situations get fast access to the financial push they need with no need to bring collateral or guarantor.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>Rosabon offers varieties of loan products, these include:</p>



<ul><li><strong>Personal loans:</strong>&nbsp;You can apply for up to ₦3,000,000 within a period of 48 hours, with a payback rate that depends on the time you repay the loan. Note that this period of repayment may span from 6 to 10 months.</li><li><strong>Group Loan:&nbsp;</strong>This allows corporate entities or partnerships to apply for huge loans to finance their businesses.</li><li><strong>Business loans:</strong>&nbsp;Allows you to fund your business with the financial push it needs.</li><li><strong>Consumer Asset loans:</strong>&nbsp;This plan gives you a chance to apply for up to ₦15,000,000 by using your car or vehicle as an asset for the loan.</li><li><strong>Credit Cash Back:&nbsp;</strong>This plan is specifically made for regular customers of Rosabon, as it allows them to apply for more loans at cheaper rates.</li></ul>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>You must possess the following to be able to apply here:</p>



<ul><li>A current bank account.</li><li>Must be between the age of 21 to 58 years.</li><li>Must have a tax ID or pension account.</li><li>Must be employed.</li><li>Must have a valid National Identity Card.</li></ul>



<h2>15. Page Financials</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="544" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-1300x544.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9626" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-1300x544.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-400x167.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-768x321.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-1536x642.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-860x360.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-430x180.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-700x293.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria-150x63.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Page-Financials-Nigeria.png 1875w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p><a href="https://creditnigeria.com/page-financials">Page Financials</a>&nbsp;is a Nigerian Fintech company that offers you quick access to personal loans, Remit Credit, and group loans. This platform promises you up to ₦5,000,000 loan within 3 hours if your loan application is approved. Note that the platform does not require stringent paperwork, collateral or guarantors.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>Page Financials gives:</p>



<ul><li><strong>Personal loans:</strong>&nbsp;Starting with a minimum of ₦200,000 and up to ₦5,000,000 and payable within a period of 3 to 12 months.</li><li><strong>Remit Credit:</strong>&nbsp;This product can only be used by customers who receive their salaries via Remita. If you do, you can apply for up to ₦2,500,000 with lower interest rates. Note that the repayment will be deducted from your salary via Remita.</li><li><strong>Group Loans:</strong>&nbsp;This service is for corporate entities and partnerships. Apply for the loan at a flat rate of 3.75% per month repayable over a period of 15 months.</li></ul>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>To apply for a loan here, you have to possess the following:</p>



<ul><li>A valid National ID card.</li><li>A bank account.</li><li>A valid phone number (registered with your bank)</li><li>A gadget with internet access.</li><li>Email address.</li></ul>



<h2>16. Grofin</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="570" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-1300x570.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9627" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-1300x570.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-400x175.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-768x337.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-1536x674.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-860x377.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-430x189.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-700x307.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria-150x66.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Grofin-Nigeria.png 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>Grofin is an internationally recognised finance company with an active branch in Nigeria and other African countries.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.grofin.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Grofin</a>&nbsp;specialises in empowering small and growing businesses (SGBs) by offering or investing a sum between $100,000 to $1.5 million on selected businesses. This is no ordinary quick loan company, and their requirement is quite more stringent than that of the other companies.</p>



<h3>Available loan types and investment criteria</h3>



<p>Grofin only considers loan applications from businesses in the following fields:</p>



<ul><li><strong>Business Profile:</strong>&nbsp;Grofin only invests in businesses with 1 to 6 years of operational experience.</li><li><strong>Geographical Location:</strong>&nbsp;Grofin only approves loan requests for businesses in Nigeria, Ghana, Zambia, Ivory Coast, Senegal, Kenya, South Africa, Rwanda, Tanzania, Jordan, Iraq, Egypt, and Omar.</li><li><strong>Business Sector:</strong>&nbsp;Grofin loans are majorly for Healthcare emergencies, Manufacturing, Energy, Education, Water/Sanitation, or Labour-intensive businesses. Other sectors may be considered if the platform deems such business fit.</li></ul>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<ul><li>Collateral &#8211; Although the value of the collateral required is not specified, it must be commensurate with the weight of the loan required.</li><li>The person applying must be within the age of 22 and 58 years.</li><li>The prospective lendee must be employed and be capable of paying back the borrowed loan within the period of time requested.</li><li>Must have a valid National ID card that states clearly the client’s home address.</li><li>Must have a valid bank account with your BVN handy.</li><li>Complete the pre-assessment questionnaire.</li><li>Complete the checklists and apply for the loan type that best suit your purpose.</li></ul>



<h2>17. Smedan</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="552" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-1300x552.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9628" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-1300x552.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-400x170.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-768x326.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-1536x652.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-860x365.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-430x183.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-700x297.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria-150x64.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Smedan-Nigeria.png 1826w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>Smedan is a Nigerian quick loan company with a strong connection with top Nigerian government agencies. This platform provides easy access to personal, business, and mortgage loans to Nigerians, either employed or unemployed. Their major aim is to “help individuals to achieve their aims and targets quickly with the necessary financial push they need.”&nbsp;</p>



<p>The payback rates are claimed to be friendly and will be determined by the sum of money you are applying for and the length of time it will take you to pay the loan back.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>On&nbsp;<a href="https://smedan.gov.ng/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Smedan,</a>&nbsp;you can apply for personal loans, business loan, mortgage loans and credit cash. Note that your request must fall within the following purposes:</p>



<ul><li>Start a Business</li></ul>



<ul><li>Expand a Business</li><li>Holiday</li><li>Household goods</li><li>Education</li><li>Car/Vehicle purchase and other purposes the platform deems fit.</li></ul>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>To get Smedan loans, the customer must:</p>



<ul><li>Provide a recent bank statement of account.</li><li>Must possess a certificate of incorporation if a company.</li><li>Must possess a valid National ID card, and</li><li>A functioning bank account.</li></ul>



<h2>18. Kiakia.com</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="491" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-1300x491.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9629" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-1300x491.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-400x151.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-768x290.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-1536x580.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-860x325.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-430x162.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-700x264.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria-150x57.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Kiakia-Nigeria.png 1875w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>“Kiakia”, a Yoruba word which means “swiftly” is the name of this Nigerian quick loan company – from their name, you know that they have a high priority for a speedy transaction. Kiakia offers Nigerians small business loans, personal loans, and creates a room for investors to lend money on their platform for future interests.&nbsp;</p>



<p>To use this platform you have to communicate directly with “Mr K”, the company’s chatbot who will reply with automated messages and process your loan application.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p><a href="https://kiakia.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kiakia</a>&nbsp;offers business and personal loans, and depending on your fixed or business income, Mr.K can offer you a minimum of ₦10,000 and a maximum of ₦5,000,000.</p>



<p>How KiaKia works: On the Kiakia website, you will see the “Apply” button, click on it and it will redirect you to a chat with Mr K. where you can either apply for a loan or invest money.</p>



<p>Requirements&nbsp;</p>



<p>Kiakia does not require too stringent requirements and you do not need a guarantor or collateral. However, you must:</p>



<ul><li>Create an account with your email address.</li><li>Be above the age of 21.</li><li>Be employed or have a business.</li><li>Possess a valid means of identification, e.g. International Passport, National ID card, or Drivers license.</li><li>Bank statement not later than 3 months.</li></ul>



<p>Note that as of November 2019, loans are not available for students on Kiakia.</p>



<h2>19. Alat-Wema</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="515" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-1300x515.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9630" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-1300x515.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-400x159.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-768x304.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-1536x609.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-860x341.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-430x170.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-700x277.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria-150x59.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Alat-wema-nigeria.png 1892w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p><a href="https://www.alat.ng/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ALAT is an instant loan product</a>&nbsp;offered by WEMA Bank Plc. This product promises personal loans of up to ₦200,000 without any stringent paperwork or collateral requirements.</p>



<h3>How Alat works</h3>



<p>Before you can use ALAT products, you need to have a WEMA bank account, it is through this account that you will get credited and debited. Now, the process for loan application goes thus:</p>



<ul><li>Sign up on the ALAT website,</li><li>Click the menu button for “Loan” options.</li><li>Check the ALAT disclaimer and T&amp;C.</li><li>The system will evaluate for you a risk score and determine your loan worthiness. This risk score will also determine the interest percentage to be deducted.</li><li>Wait for your loan request to be approved.</li><li>Get your money within a few minutes.</li></ul>



<p>Note that failure to pay at the agreed time may lead to automatic deduction of the cash from your bank account.</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<ul><li>Have a valid means of identification, eg. A national ID card or Driver’s License.</li><li>Must be above the age of 21.</li><li>A photo of a recent utility bill (not later than 3 months), with an address matching your ALAT profile.</li></ul>



<p><strong>Freebies&nbsp;</strong></p>



<p>You can win extra cash by referring your family and friends to also use ALAT products. Get ₦500 for every friend you refer with your referral code. The person you refer also get ₦200 after their first transaction with the platform.</p>



<h2>20. Payconnect</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1300" height="500" src="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-1300x500.png" alt="" class="wp-image-9631" srcset="https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-1300x500.png 1300w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-400x154.png 400w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-768x295.png 768w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-1536x591.png 1536w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-860x331.png 860w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-430x165.png 430w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-700x269.png 700w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria-150x58.png 150w, https://creditnigeria.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/payconnect-nigeria.png 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1300px) 100vw, 1300px" /></figure>



<p>Payconnect is a Nigerian quick loan company that targets salary earners, the platform requires no collateral requirement or guarantors. Just have a valid bank account and apply from ₦5,000 up to ₦10,000 payable within a period of 30 days.</p>



<h3>Available loan types</h3>



<p>Payconnect offers personal and business loans, however, before your loan application can be approved here, you must first get your employer’s consent or show your certificate of incorporation. Note also, that the payback interest rate is determined by the nature of your loan request and the time frame it takes to return. Payconnect promises to give you higher loans if you pay back early (50% more each time you apply).</p>



<h3>Requirements</h3>



<p>To obtain Payconnect loans you have to:</p>



<ul><li>Be above the age of 18.</li><li>Be employed.</li><li>Submit a Valid Staff card or certificate of incorporation if a company.</li><li>Submit Bank statement not later than 3 months.</li><li>Must have a valid National ID card.</li><li>Must have a bank account with at least ₦100 in it with a BVN.</li><li>Must be a Nigerian earning income in Nigeria.</li></ul>



<h2>Before committing to a loan</h2>



<p>Now that you have good knowledge about quick loan lenders in Nigeria, the next&nbsp; step is to:</p>



<ul><li>Check what each platform has to offer you and how you can best maximise the opportunities you are offered.</li><li>Make sure you confirm the payback interest rates and all fees that apply to each loan&nbsp;</li><li>Be sure you actually need the money you are applying for and you have the required capacity to pay back.</li><li>If you notice anything fishy about a platform, search online for reviews about them and avoid the ones with too many bad reviews.</li><li>If the payback rate is not convenient for you, avoid taking the loan totally.</li></ul>
